snippet.textDisplay:
Yup, this one is the best svt cover from gg imo. The way they successfully interpret svt's "weird" vibe is outstanding. In addition, they didn't lose their own charms somehow, and thus this performance is very enjoyable. Their body flow (?) is by far the closest to svt's. They know when to dance more powerful and when to dance more flowy like a water lmao. While other group, they tried and that's, in fact, very cool. But the way they perform this song is not balanced, like they either perform it too powerful or too soft imo. And their voice, omg, I'M SO IN LOVE. They surely know this song better than any other group.

Edit: Seventeen is like Red Velvet. Their song concept is refreshing. But most groups misunderstand it as cute concept that's why they kinda fail to reach svt's and rv's style (and that's why svt slay rv's song like ice cream cake etc). And RCPC, they know how to do refreshing concept, they enjoy the performance sm, that's why this one is cool.

what i learned with this video is :
"yunkyoung should be center" she's really a main dancer..and she kind of capture your attention most than the other when she dances in the center position like an anchor. 
"Sohee should rap" i don't like her tone when she sings (a bit cringy to me) but when she raps..i love her tone..
"that's the type of songs they should go for" i didn't really like their title song but this cover really suits their style, they should go for it!
Last but not least "covering svt is always a good choice but it's hard"!
